&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commercial pilot certificate and instrument rating for category and class of aircraft&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current FAA Class I or II Medical Certificate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2000 total flight hours or meets CAMTS equivalency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1500 hours Helicopter flight hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1000 hours PIC in category&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;500 hours of rotorcraft turbine time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;200 hours of cross country&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50 hours of unaided night can be accepted with a minimum of 100 hours of aided night&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50 hours of hood or actual time instrument time in flight in category. &amp;nbsp;(Simulator time does not count.) A pilot that is dual qualified in fixed wing with 100 hours of actual instrument time can reduce this requirement to 25 hours.&lt;/li&gt;
