&lt;p data-start=&quot;197&quot; data-end=&quot;572&quot;&gt;As a Base Lead Pilot at Life Link III, you play a critical dual role—serving as a highly skilled Pilot in Command while also leading and supporting the day-to-day operations of your assigned base. You are a trusted leader, ensuring operational excellence, regulatory compliance, and a strong team culture rooted in safety, collaboration, and accountability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;574&quot; data-end=&quot;886&quot;&gt;You act as the primary point of contact for pilots at your base, helping to resolve challenges, support team development, and elevate concerns when needed. Through your leadership, you help create a high-performing, mission-driven environment that supports exceptional patient care and safe transport operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Impact&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated leadership capability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages rotor wing pilot schedules for the base&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Timely entry of base schedule in Flight &amp;amp; Duty Tracker.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First level review of timecards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists the base pilots in the performance of their duties.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops and keeps updated base adverse weather plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads and models professional, productive, and team-orientated behaviors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts 621 Training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborates with the Clinical Base Lead to provide aviation updates for base meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate any aviation updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops and maintains a ‘Local Area Hazards Map”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures new pilots receive base orientation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures medical equipment is weighed as specified in Section 4 of the GOM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audits Life Link III Flight &amp;amp; Duty Tracker for accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures policies and procedures are followed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedules and leads monthly Base Operations Meeting in collaboration with the ACP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completes all necessary paperwork/administrative responsibilities are completed timely&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in HAA operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior Search and Rescue Experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ATP Certificate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Base Pay Rate: $54.06 - $74.83 per hour, based on experience (b&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;ase lead pay is a $2.50 stipend added to current hourly rate)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li
